About the job
WHO'S SHOPFULLY? 📍

ShopFully is the tech company leader in Drive To Store 🛒 that connects millions of shoppers with the stores around them. We help people save time and money and make smarter shopping decisions and we support retailers and brands engaging with consumers throughout the customer journey, from online research to in-store shopping.

With our proprietary websites and apps, a network of publishers and digital platforms and our proprietary tech solutions, we reach 200 millions users globally.

We joined MEDIA Central Group in 2023 and we are now a partner to over 500 top retailers and brands in 25 countries across Europe 🇪🇺, Australia 🇦🇺 and Latin America 🇧🇷.

But we keep on growing, as a matter of fact, we’ve recently teamed up with Flipp, landing into the US 🇺🇸 and Canadian 🇨🇦 markets, with the aim of creating an advanced digital merchandising network that will revolutionize how retailers and brands with consumers.

We’re a team of over 450 people focused on Digital Retail, spanning 30 different nationalities, with a mission: reinventing local shopping worldwide.

If you want to work in a fast-growing and international environment, that’s the right place for you.
Are you ready to join us? 🚀


TO FEEL AT HOME 🛋️ IN SHOPFULLY YOU SHOULD 

ACT AS AN OWNER: no challenge is too big for you! We set clear goals and finish what we start. We go the extra-mile and fix what doesn't work: that's how we achieve great results;

RELY ON DATA: let the data do the talking, so we think, plan and act supported by fact checked data and we value calculated risk taking. We measure our success to keep improving;

PLAY TOGETHER: magic happens in teams! That’s why we communicate clearly and support each other. We believe in sharing helpful feedback and building trust. Together we are unstoppable.

WHAT YOU'LL FIND AT SHOPFULLY 🫶

🌎 An opportunity to build your experience in an internationally growing scale-up company;
🕶️ A young and informal work environment;
🏡 Flexible work arrangements encouraging smart and/or full-remote working;
🍕 Meal vouchers (yes, also while working remotely!);
💻 Company laptop and all you need to set up a proper home-working station;
💡 1.5 hour of Learning Time per week.


WHAT YOU'LL DO 💪🏻

We are currently looking for a highly motivated, curious and proactive Junior Sales & Marketing Analyst to join our Strategic Partnership Management Team with an internship.

This role requires a unique combination of analytical skills and strong interpersonal abilities, as you will be responsible for both data analysis and direct interactions with internal stakeholders and external clients.

In this role you will support the team focused in the Portuguese market 🇵🇹 in:

 Interpreting all the data of campaigns from different sources (tableau, internal DB analytics...) to deliver reporting and analysis with “powerful” insight;

 Preparing final presentation to be delivered to the customers. Review, synthesize and communicate insights in meaningful and actionable ways (transform data and results into actionable insights);

 Reading signals from the market to detect cultural trends and shifts in our customers expectations in terms of data


WHAT YOU'LL NEED 🪄

University Degree in Marketing, Economics, ICT and related fields;
High knowledge of Excel and an analytical and data-driven mindset;
A proactive and problem-solving mindset, with attention to detail;
Portuguese: Fluent, both written and spoken;
Spanish: Fluent, both written and spoken;
English: Good, both written and spoken.

WHAT WOULD HELP YOU THE MOST 🙌🏻

Basic knowledge of data analysis and data visualizations tools (i.e.Tableau) would be considered a plus;
Good communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to engage with both technical and non-technical audiences.


🌎 LOCATION: We have an office in Barcellona but you can take advantage of our flexible hybrid mode.

ShopFully will process your personal data for this application as indicated in the Privacy Notice pursuant to Arts. 13 and 14 of Regulation EU 2016/679 and that you can view here
